                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17801206-18-off93 t17801206-18-victim199"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            ,</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17801206-18-person200">
                  CATHERINE
                   DELEVITT
               <interp inst="t17801206-18-person200" type="surname" value="DELEVITT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17801206-18-person200" type="given" value="CATHERINE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17801206-18-person200" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I was behind the house drying linen. The shop is forward where my husband worked. I saw the prisoner skipping across the door with a bundle under his arm. I looked into the shop and missed the great coat. I had seen it there but just before. My husband was out of the shop at the time. I pursued the<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178012060018"></xptr> prisoner immediately, and took him with the great coat under his arm.</p>
               <p>Another Witness sworn.</p>
               <p>I saw the great coat upon his arm. Upon being taken he threw it down.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I am not guilty of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17801206-18-verdict94" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17801206-18-verdict94" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Tried by the Second Middlesex Jury before Mr. 
